Package org.opengis.feature

Interface DynamicAttributeType<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of attribute values.
    All Superinterfaces:
    AttributeType<V>, IdentifiedType, PropertyType
    @Classifier(METACLASS)
@UML(identifier="AttributeType",
     specification=OGC_14083)
public interface DynamicAttributeType<V>
extends AttributeType<V>
    Definition of a dynamic attribute in a moving feature type. Dynamic attributes describe attributes of a feature in which the values vary with time and/or location. A Feature having dynamic attributes is a moving feature. A moving feature can have an arbitrary amount of time-varying attributes, such as the velocity of vehicles or the wind speed of hurricanes.

    Dynamic attributes are used for non-spatial attribute. If the value type of a dynamic attribute is geometric point, it is a trajectory.

    Since:
    3.1
    See Also:
    DynamicAttribute, AttributeType
